{
  "texts": [
    "Human feedback is valuable for aligning LLMs.",
    "Traditionally, this feedback is derived from human preferences as to the quality of LLM responses.",
    "In this work, we employ AI feedback through a refined version of the finance reasoning instruction dataset described in Section 3.2.",
    "Along with the output generated by GPT-4 (Ope-nAI, 2023c), we generate responses using the FinMA-7B (Xie et al., 2023) and LLaMa-7Bchat (Touvron et al., 2023) models to each prompt.",
    "For a given prompt, the GPT-4 output is selected as the 'chosen' response while we select randomly one from FinMA-7B and LLaMa outputs as the 'rejected' response."
  ]
}